00:17:00.240 --> 00:17:02.430
awakening was soaked with prayer. When

00:17:02.440 --> 00:17:05.390
Charles Finney preached, fire fell. But

00:17:05.400 --> 00:17:07.310
I assure you, the match had already been

00:17:07.320 --> 00:17:09.669
struck in the prayer chamber. My knees

00:17:09.679 --> 00:17:12.189
broke the ground before his voice did.

00:17:12.199 --> 00:17:14.669
My tears watered the soil of souls

00:17:14.679 --> 00:17:17.510
before he ever saw their faces. I was

00:17:17.520 --> 00:17:19.429
not his assistant; I was his

00:17:19.439 --> 00:17:20.796
intercessor.

00:17:20.839 --> 00:17:23.390
And I have come in this hour—yes, this

00:17:23.400 --> 00:17:25.470
exact moment in history—to speak to

00:17:25.480 --> 00:17:27.750
those who feel hidden, overlooked,

00:17:27.760 --> 00:17:30.230
passed by. To those who are tired of

00:17:30.240 --> 00:17:33.190
shallow altars and powerless gatherings.

00:17:33.200 --> 00:17:36.070
To those who have felt the tug of God to

00:17:36.080 --> 00:17:39.030
weep in secret, fast in silence, and

00:17:39.040 --> 00:17:41.310
shake the unseen realm.

00:17:41.320 --> 00:17:44.070
